Great! You're already using *Python* with *Flask* in this web app.

Here’s a *step-by-step guide* to run your Flask app using *Python* only:

---

✅ *1. Install Flask (One-Time Setup)*

In your terminal or command prompt, run:

```bash
pip install flask
```

---

✅ *2. Save Your Python File*

Create a file called *`app.py`* and paste this code:

```python
from flask import Flask, render_template, request

app = Flask(_name_)

def recommend_course(percentage, goal, interest):
    if percentage < 40:
        return "Focus on basic skill-building courses."

    if goal == "job":
        if interest == "computer":
            return "BCA, BSc IT, or Software Development"
        elif interest == "electronics":
            return "Diploma or BSc in Electronics"
        elif interest == "commerce":
            return "BBA or BCom"
        else:
            return "Basic certification courses"

    elif goal == "higher studies":
        if interest == "math":
            return "B.Tech CSE or Data Science"
        elif interest == "biology":
            return "BSc Biotech or Microbiology"
        else:
            return "BA/BSc in your subject"

    elif goal == "business":
        return "BBA or Entrepreneurship course"

    else:
        return "Enter valid goal and interest"






<head><title>Result</title></head>
<body>
    <h2>Your Recommended Course:</h2>
    <p>{{ course }}</p>
    <a href="/">Back</a>
</body>
</html>
```

---

▶️ *4. Run the App*

In terminal:
```bash
python app.py
```

Open browser:  
👉 `http://127.0.0.1:5000`


















@app.route('/')
def home():
    return render_template('index.html')

@app.route('/recommend', methods=['POST'])
def recommend():
    percentage = float(request.form['percentage'])
    goal = request.form['goal'].lower()
    interest = request.form['interest'].lower()

    course = recommend_course(percentage, goal, interest)
    return render_template('result.html', course=course)

if _name_ == '_main_':
    app.run(debug=True)
```

---

✅ *3. Create HTML Files*

Inside your project folder, create a folder named *`templates`*, and inside it, add:

`index.html`:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head><title>Course Recommender</title></head>
<body>
    <h2>Course Recommendation</h2>
    <form action="/recommend" method="post">
        <label>Percentage:</label><br>
        <input type="text" name="percentage"><br><br>
        <label>Goal:</label><br>
        <select name="goal">
            <option value="job">Job</option>
            <option value="higher studies">Higher Studies</option>
            <option value="business">Business</option>
        </select><br><br>
        <label>Interest:</label><br>
        <input type="text" name="interest"><br><br>
        <input type="submit" value="Submit">
    </form>
</body>
</html>
```

`result.html`:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
